Description: Shoulder sherd of East Greek or perhaps local pottery closed vessel with turn to neck; interior reserved; exterior: on white slip, part of a tree with spreading branches and some further worn motif (glaze fired pale red/orange); band of same colour at transition to neck.
Bibliographic references: Vase / Catalogue of Vases in the British Museum (B102.30)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.621)
